title: Phish 2014-11-02 MGM Grand Garden Arena, Las Vegas, NV SBD
description:
Phish
11/02/14
MGM Grand Garden Arena
Las Vegas, NV


Set 1: 

Runaway Jim
Foam
Mexican Cousin
Ocelot
Sugar Shack
Song I Heard The Ocean Sing
Halfway To The Moon
Bathtub Gin
Free
Walls Of A Cave

Set 2:

Chalk Dust Torture# >
Piper >
Theme From The Bottom >
Wombat
David Bowie
The Line 
You Enjoy Myself

Encore:

Moma Dance >
Slave To The Traffic Light


[#] Unfinished.

Mexican Cousin was played for the first time since June 19, 2012 (110 shows). Page teased Rhapsody In Blue at the end of Halfway to the Moon. Free, Walls of the Cave, Bowie and YEM all contained Martian Monster quotes. Chalk Dust was unfinished. Toward the end of the YEM jam, Trey picked up his megaphone and began using the siren on it as he ran around the stage, eventually coming to Mike and holding it up to the bass. Mike then put his bass down and began playing his fight bell with drum sticks while Trey went and started drumming along with Fishman.  Eventually Mike and Page joined in, so that all four were playing on Fish's kit. Moma Dance was played for the first time ever as an encore.
